    {
      "name": "Escalating Urgency",
      "category": "Structure",
      "description": "Each sentence should raise the stakes beyond the previous one, building vertical pressure rather than cataloguing facts at equal weight and temperature. By the time the proposed work appears, reviewers should feel the problem is urgent enough that the solution feels inevitable \u2014 'almost frustrated on behalf of patients.' The gap must be felt, not just named.",
