      "name": "Structural Resilience of Aims",
      "category": "Structure",
      "description": "Each aim should feel like a complete thought that produces a usable artifact \u2014 a framework, methodology, or characterized dataset \u2014 with independent value, not just a setup for subsequent aims. The relationship between aims should be one of building and refinement, not hard dependency. Failure mode awareness should be conveyed through language that signals intellectual flexibility and confidence, not defensiveness or hedging.",
